text.tspan: Generic chart title to silence errors
Total mortality rates by cause of death, measured as the number of deaths per 100,000 population. Death rates are
given as all-age rates (not age-standardized). Data for specific causes of death may be missing or intermittent where
it enters or falls out of the top 10 reported causes of deaths in any year.
